bubble-configurator-wcube-step_material.title: Wandcube Holzart w=C3=A4hlen
bubble-configurator-wcube-step_material.headline: Materials
bubble-configurator-wcube-step_material.text: Select the material you require. We also offer many materials in different colours.

bubble-configurator-wcube-step_color.title: Wandcube Farbe w=C3=A4hlen
bubble-configurator-wcube-step_color.headline: Colors
bubble-configurator-wcube-step_color.text:
To preserve the grain of the solid woods, they are varnished as standard. On request we also offer our veneers varnished.

We offer lacquered MDF in over 200 RAL colors. The lacquers are environmentally-friendly and opaque.

If you would like our MDF coated in another color, we will be happy to check it and source it for you.

bubble-configurator-wcube-step_thickness.title: Wandcube Materialst=C3=A4rke
bubble-configurator-wcube-step_thickness.text: Specify the wood thickness for your cube here.

bubble-configurator-wcube-step_width_dep.title: Wandcube Ma=C3=9Fe
bubble-configurator-wcube-step_width_dep.text: Select the dimensions of your wall shelving and decide whether you require a white back wall panel.

bubble-configurator-wcube-help.title: Wandcube Hilfe
bubble-configurator-wcube-help.text: We use invisible fixtures for wall-mounted units. Combine your cubes with a variety of colours to keep your favourite objects safe and secure.

bubble-configurator-wboard-step_material.title: Wandboard Holzart w=C3=A4hlen
bubble-configurator-wboard-step_material.headline: Materials
bubble-configurator-wboard-step_material.text: Select the material you require. We also offer many materials in different colours.

bubble-configurator-wboard-step_color.title: Wandboard Farben w=C3=A4hlen
bubble-configurator-wboard-step_color.headline: Colours
bubble-configurator-wboard-step_color.text:
To preserve the grain of the solid woods, they are varnished as standard. On request we can also offer our veneers varnished.

We offer lacquered MDF in over 200 RAL colors. The lacquers are environmentally-friendly and opaque.

If you would like our MDF coated in another color, we will be happy to check it for you.

bubble-configurator-wboard-step_thicknes.title: Wandboard Materialst=C3=A4rke
bubble-configurator-wboard-step_thicknes.headline: Material thickness
bubble-configurator-wboard-step_thicknes.text: For our wall-mounted shelves the material thickness is always 3 cm.

bubble-configurator-wboard-step_width_de.title: Wandboard Ma=C3=9Fe
bubble-configurator-wboard-step_width_de.headline: Dimensions
bubble-configurator-wboard-step_width_de.text: Select the width and depth of your wall-mounted shelf here.

bubble-configurator-wboard-help.title: Wandboard Hilfe
bubble-configurator-wboard-help.text: We use invisible fixtures for wall-mounted shelves. We determine the number of mountings required from the width of the shelf. The maximum load is 15 kg.

bubble-configurator-rboden-step_color.title: Regalb=C3=B6den Farben w=C3=A4hlen
bubble-configurator-rboden-step_color.headline: Colours
bubble-configurator-rboden-step_color.text:
To preserve the grain of the solid woods, they are varnished as standard. On request we can also offer our veneers varnished.

We offer lacquered MDF in over 200 RAL colors. The lacquers are environmentally-friendly and opaque.

If you would like our MDF coated in another color, we will be happy to check and source it for you.

bubble-configurator-rboden-step_thicknes.title: Regalb=C3=B6den Materialst=C3=A4rke
bubble-configurator-rboden-step_thicknes.headline: Material thickness
bubble-configurator-rboden-step_thicknes.text: Please specify the wood thickness for your shelves here.

bubble-configurator-rboden-step_width_de.title: Regalb=C3=B6den Ma=C3=9Fe
bubble-configurator-rboden-step_width_de.text: Please select the width and depth of your shelves.

bubble-configurator-rboden-help.title: Regalb=C3=B6den Hilfe
bubble-configurator-rboden-help.text: We produce your shelves to the precise dimensions that you select. The edges are finished with a subtle chamfer. If you have special a special request, please contact us.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_materi.title: Regale Schritt 3 material wood
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_materi.text:
A matching wood/colour combination is pre-selected for doors, drawers and main body as standard.
You can however, change the wood/colour combination for doors and drawers here.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_materi.title: Regale Schritt 3 material glass
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_materi.text: The glass door is manufactured with clear glass, with a thickness of 6 mm. If you prefer clear glass in a thickness of 4 mm or 5 mm, please speak to our specialist furniture consultants. Glass doors are supplied with a handle.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_shelf_.title: Regale Schritt 3 shelf options open
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_shelf_.text: No door will be fitted; the compartment remains open.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_shelf_.title: Regale Schritt 3 shelf options double doors
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_shelf_.text: The maximum width for an overlying hinged door is 120 cm. The door consists of your natural wood or MDF in the respective RAL colour. It can also be fitted with a 6mm thick glass door.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_shelf_.title: Regale Schritt 3 shelf options simple doors
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_shelf_.text: Surface mounted door, must have a width between 25-60 cm and a height between 25-100 cm. The door consists of your chosen natural wood or MDF in the respective RAL colour or can be fitted with a 6mm thick glass door.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_shelf_.title: Regale Schritt 3 shelf options drawer
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_shelf_.text: Drawers can be manufactured for shelving units with a minimum depth of 30 cm. The maximum height is 60 cm, and the maximum load is 30 kg. The front consists of the selected solid wood or MDF in your chosen colour; the body is made in chipboard.

bubble-configurator-regale-width.title: Regale Schritt 1 gesamte Breite
bubble-configurator-regale-width.text: Please enter the total width from the left-hand outer edge to the right-hand outer edge, in cms. Conversions will be made in the configurator so that all further steps maintain this overall width.

bubble-configurator-regale-height.title: Regale Schritt 1 gesamte H=C3=B6he
bubble-configurator-regale-height.headline: Total Height
bubble-configurator-regale-height.text: Please enter the total height from the highest to the lowest point of the shelf in cms. All further steps will be calculated so that the total height is not exceeded. A plinth of 7 cm is included in the total height. Side walls must be divided from a height of 300 cm for solid wood, 275 cm for MDF (decor + lacquered surfaces) and 250 cm for plywood.

bubble-configurator-regale-depth.title: Regale Schritt 1 Tiefe
bubble-configurator-regale-depth.text: In specifying the depth of the shelving you are determining how much storage space you require front-to-back. Please note that the full depth is only available if you do not select a back wall panel (in step 4). If you choose a back wall panel, you should expect to lose approximately 0.5 cm of depth. For a CD shelf you require approx. 15 cm depth. For document files, plan for over 30 cm depth. If you are uncertain, base your specification on the deepest object that you expect to place on your shelving. Hint: Many customers opt for a depth of 25 cm.

bubble-configurator-regale-thickness_3_3.title: Regale Schritt 1 Materialst=C3=A4rke 3 3 2
bubble-configurator-regale-thickness_3_3.text: All external surfaces (top, bottom, left and right) and all vertical cheeks are 3 cm thick and only the shelves themselves measure 2 cm thick.

bubble-configurator-regale-thickness_3_2.title: Regale Schritt 1 Materialst=C3=A4rke 3 2 2
bubble-configurator-regale-thickness_3_2.text: Only the four external surfaces (top, bottom, left and right) are 3 cm thick; all other parts are 2 cm thick (vertical internal cheeks and shelves).

bubble-configurator-regale-step_material.title: Regale Schritt 1 Holzart w=C3=A4hlen
bubble-configurator-regale-step_material.text: Select your personal favourite from up to 12 wood types. If you are unsure which timber suits you and your existing furniture best, simply read through the information pages at https://www.pickawood.com/en/quality/types-of-wood to find out more about their special qualities. You can also contact our specialist furniture consultants to order up to four free wood samples.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_color.title: Regale Schritt 1 Farbe w=C3=A4hlen
bubble-configurator-regale-step_color.text: Choose your preferred colour from a wide range of options. Our solid timber is varnished as standard to ensure that the grain is preserved. This also ensures that your furniture item is individual and unique. If you would prefer a clear varnish or a paint finish from one of our 200 RAL colours, please contact us. With MDF, you can choose a matt coating or the whole colour range in painted RAL colours. Our paint is opaque and environmentally-friendly.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_thicknes.title: Regale Schritt 1 Materialst=C3=A4rke
bubble-configurator-regale-step_thicknes.text: We offer solid wood in thicknesses of 2 cm or 3 cm. With MDF and plywood the material thickness is approx. 1.8-2.0 cm or 2.8-3.0 cm, depending on the surface treatment. Your entered external dimensions remain unchanged.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_help.title: Regale Schritt 1 Hilfe
bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_help.text: For a CD shelf you need a depth of 15 cm; for document files the depth should be at least 25 cm. The unit is assembled on its side. When specifying the overall height, you should allow a clearance to the ceiling to allow the shelf to be stood upright comfortably during fitting.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_2_help.title: Regale Schritt 2 Hilfe
bubble-configurator-regale-step_2_help.text: The number in the compartment shows the internal height of the compartment. Please always calculate compartment heights starting at the top and working downwards. You change the height of an entire section using the model.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_2_width.title: Regale Schritt 2 Breite (cm)
bubble-configurator-regale-step_2_width.text: Specify the width of the current section of the shelving unit here. This width is the internal width between the two outer sides from left to right.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_2_height.title: Regale Schritt 2 H=C3=B6he (cm)
bubble-configurator-regale-step_2_height.text: Here you can specify the height of every shelf-column. This is the total height, including all compartments and the thickness of the wood.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_2_cubby_.title: Regale Schritt 2 F=C3=A4cher
bubble-configurator-regale-step_2_cubby_.text: Specify how many compartments you would like for your products. You may opt for just a few compartments or for many in one row - the choice is yours!

bubble-configurator-regale-step_2_socket.title: Regale Schritt 2 Sockel
bubble-configurator-regale-step_2_socket.headline: Plinths
bubble-configurator-regale-step_2_socket.text: Our shelves are available with or without plinths. The plinth has a regular height of 7 cm. The plinth height of 7 cm is included in the total height of your product. On request, we can also adapt your plinth to the height of your skirting board, please contact out specialist furniture consultants to arrange this.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_help.title: Regale Schritt 3 Hilfe
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_help.text: For a CD shelf you need a depth of 15 cm; for document files the depth should be at least 25 cm. The unit is assembled on its side. If you wish to have a door that covers multiple compartments, drag with the mouse over the relevant compartments to select them.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_help.title: Regale Schritt 4 Hilfe
bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_help.text: Our shelving strip with mounting holes lets you adjust the shelf heights in increments of 32 mm (the spacing between each hole). If you choose mounting holes, a central row of shelves will nevertheless be fixed in place in larger units to maintain stability.

bubble-configurator-regale-column_count.title: Regale Schritt 2 Anzahl der Spalten insgesamt
bubble-configurator-regale-column_count.headline: Sections
bubble-configurator-regale-column_count.text: Specify how many vertical sections you would like in your wardrobe unit. An initial design is suggested in the configurator, which you can then modify freely.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_handle.title: Regale Schritt 3 =C3=96ffnung/Griff Eingriff
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_handle.text: With this option we will cut a small opening in the door. You can then use this to open the door with your fingers.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_handle.title: Regale Schritt 3 =C3=96ffnung/Griff Metallgriff
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_handle.text: A chrome metal handle with a simple and stylish design helps you open the door.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_handle.title: Regale Schritt 3 =C3=96ffnung/Griff Pushtoopen
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_handle.headline: Push to open
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_handle.text: Our 'push-to-open' technology can be activated with a light push. There is no need for door knobs, meaning doors can remain a subtle and integrated feature.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_handle.title: Regale Schritt 3 =C3=96ffnung/Griff Knauf
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_handle.text: A chrome metal door knob in a simple design provides a stylish finish.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_rear_c.title: Regale Schritt 4 R=C3=BCckwand
bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_rear_c.headline: Back wall colors
bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_rear_c.text: Please choose one of our back panel colours. Our recessed back panels are made of 3 mm thick hardboard. Please note that the shelf decreases in depth by 19 mm with a back panel. To increase stability, we recommend adding a back panel for furniture with 1 and 2 columns.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_lochle.title: Regale Schritt 4 Lochreihe
bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_lochle.headline: Shelving strips with mounting holes
bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_lochle.text: The vertical hole strip allows you more freedom in arranging your individual shelves. Holes are drilled at 32 mm intervals, allowing you to adjust the sizes of the compartments to suit your needs. Please note that if you select a shelving strip with mounting holes, any compartment heights you have previously set will no longer be relevant. In high shelving units, a horizontal compartment row is also fixed in place to retain the best possible stability.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_raumte.title: Regale Schritt 4 Raumteiler
bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_raumte.headline: Room divider
bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_raumte.text: For the room divider option we manufacture the baseboard (if selected) to be included on both sides of the product. In addition, all doors are mirrored, so that you can use them identically on both sides. Drawers are offered exclusively on one side of the product. The back of the drawer consists of a solid back panel that matches the look of the drawer front.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_hanger.title: Regale Schritt 4 H=C3=A4ngeregal
bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_hanger.headline: Only available for shelves with plinths
bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_hanger.text: When you configure your shelf as a wall shelf, wall brackets are built into the vertical side panels so you can attach your shelf to the wall. The number and position of the brackets is chosen by our carpenters so that the weight is optimally distributed. Please note that wall racks can only be mounted on solid walls.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_fuslei.title: Regale Schritt 4 Fu=C3=9Fleiste
bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_fuslei.text: We can offer a skirting board cut-out for your shelf so that it can align with your wall. Simply enter the height and depth in centimetres that you would like removed. If the height of the cut-out is more than 7 cm and you decide on an additional rear wall, please contact a specialist furniture consultant, as this will affect the construction of the product.

bubble-configurator-table-general-toolti.title: Tisch tooltip
bubble-configurator-table-general-toolti.text: Standard dining tables have dimensions of 160 cm in length, 90 cm in width, and 75cm in height. There is space for 6 people to be placed at the table.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_durchd.title: Durchgehende Deck-/Bodenplatte
bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_durchd.headline: Continuous top and bottom plate
bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_durchd.text: We build racks column by column as standard. On request, we also offer continuous top and bottom plates. In this case a minimum space of 5cm to the ceiling is required for installation. Please note that continuous top and bottom plate are also split from a length of 2.75m (MDF) and 3.00m (solid). In this case we divide either centrally or symmetrically twice, depending on the number of columns.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_material.title: Regale Material - Furnier
bubble-configurator-regale-step_material.headline: Veneer
bubble-configurator-regale-step_material.text: Our real wood veneers are an economical alternative to solid wood. Our real wood veneers are attached to high-quality MDF boards. All veneers are treated with natural oils.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_material.title: Regale Material - Massive
bubble-configurator-regale-step_material.headline: Solid wood
bubble-configurator-regale-step_material.text: Our selection of solid woods are extremely durable and stable. All wood types are available with a natural, transparent oil treatment. In some cases certain wood types can also be treated with coloured oil.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_material.title: Regale Material - MDF
bubble-configurator-regale-step_material.headline: MDF
bubble-configurator-regale-step_material.text: MDF is a very stable and economical  wood alternative. We offer this material in a variety of coatings as well as painted RAL colors.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_elemen.title: Regale Schritt 3 Element type
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_elemen.headline: Arranging compartments
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_elemen.text:
You can choose how to adapt and arrange your compartments. 
For our doors and drawers, we use our 'push-to-open' technology, which allows you to open and close with just a little pressure. No handles or door knobs are required.

bubble-configurator-wood-patchwork.title: Patchwork
bubble-configurator-wood-patchwork.headline: Patchwork
bubble-configurator-wood-patchwork.text: Finger jointed wood panels. The slats are joined in length.

bubble-configurator-sideboard-legs.title: Sidaboard Schritt 2 F=C3=BC=C3=9Fe oder Sockel
bubble-configurator-sideboard-legs.headline: Stability
bubble-configurator-sideboard-legs.text: For stability reasons sometimes we add supports or pillars to your product.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_hohenv.title: H=C3=B6henversteller
bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_hohenv.headline: Only available for shelves with plinths
bubble-configurator-regale-step_4_hohenv.text: By adding the height adjuster you can adapt the height of the product to the floor. The height adjuster will generally add 0.55mm to the total height of the shelf.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_mate.title: Schrank Schritt 3 material wood
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_mate.text:
A matching wood/colour combination is pre-selected for doors, drawers and main body as standard.
You can however, change the wood/colour combination for doors and drawers here.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_mate.title: Schrank Schritt 3 material glass
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_mate.text: Glass door in manufactured with clear glass and thickness of 6 mm. If you prefer clear glass in a thickness of 4 mm or 5 mm, please speak to our specialist furniture consultants. Glass doors are supplied with a handle.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_shel.title: Schrank Schritt 3 shelf options open
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_shel.text:
No door will be fitted; the
compartment remains open.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_shel.title: Schrank Schritt 3 shelf options double doors
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_shel.headline: Hinged doors
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_shel.text: The surface-mounted door is made of your selected real wood or MDF in the respective RAL colour, it can also be supplied with a 6 mm thick glass door. The maximum door width is 120 cm.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_shel.title: Schrank Schritt 3 shelf options simple doors
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_shel.text: A surface mounted door with outside compartment must have a width between 25-60 cm and height between 25-100 cm. The door consists of your selected real wood or MDF in the appropriate RAL colour, or can be selected with 6 mm thick glass.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_shel.title: Schrank Schritt 3 shelf options drawer
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_shel.headline: Outside drawers
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_shel.text: Drawers can be manufactured for shelving units with a minimum depth of 30 cm. The maximum height is 60 cm, and the maximum load is 30 kg. The front consists of your selected solid wood or MDF in your chosen colour; the body is made in chipboard.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-width.title: Schrank Schritt 1 gesamte Breite
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-width.headline: Total width
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-width.text: Specify the total width for your cabinet. All further steps are calculated so that the total width is not exceeded. In order to be able to install the cabinet in a wall niche as well without any problems, you need a mounting distance of 3 cm on both sides.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-height.title: Schrank Schritt 1 gesamte H=C3=B6he
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-height.headline: Total height
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-height.text: Please enter the total height from the highest to the lowest point of the cabinet in cms. All further steps are calculated so that the total height is not exceeded. A plinth of 7 cm is included in the total height. Please note a mounting space of 3 cm is required from the ceiling (10 cm for sliding doors).

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-depth.title: Schrank Schritt 1 Tiefe
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-depth.headline: Depth
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-depth.text: In specifying the depth of the wardrobe you are specifying how much storage space you require front-to-back. Here you specify only the depth of the wardrobe body excluding doors/drawers or sliding doors. For doors you have to add 2 cm and for sliding doors 6 cm.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-thickness_3.title: Schrank Schritt 1 Materialst=C3=A4rke 3 3 2
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-thickness_3.text: All external surfaces (top, bottom, left and right) and all vertical cheeks are 3 cm thick and only the shelves themselves are 2 cm thick.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-thickness_3.title: Schrank Schritt 1 Materialst=C3=A4rke 3 2 2
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-thickness_3.text: Only the four external surfaces (top, bottom, left and right) are 3 cm thick; all other parts are 2 cm thick (vertical internal cheeks and shelves).

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_materi.title: Schrank Schritt 1 Holzart w=C3=A4hlen
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_materi.headline: Material selection
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_materi.text: Choose from our different surfaces. Decors are always produced on chipboard. Lacquered surfaces and solid wood veneers on MDF boards.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_color.title: Schrank Schritt 1 Farbe w=C3=A4hlen
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_color.headline: Colours
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_color.text:
In order to preserve the grain of our real wood materials, they are varnished with a natural oil as standard. On request we also offer our veneers varnished.

We offer lacquered MDF in over 200 RAL colours. The lacquers are environmentally friendly and opaque.

If you prefer our decors in a different colour, we will be happy to source it for you.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_thickn.title: Schrank Schritt 1 Materialst=C3=A4rke
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_thickn.headline: Material thickness
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_thickn.text: We always offer wardrobes in 2 cm thickness. Also our fronts have a thickness of 2 cm.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_1_help.title: Schrank Schritt 1 Hilfe
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_1_help.text:
For a CD shelf you need a depth of 15 cm; for document files the depth should be at least 25 cm.
The unit is assembled on its side. When specifying the overall height, you should allow a clearance space to the ceiling to allow the shelf to be stood upright during fitting.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_help.title: Schrank Schritt 2 Hilfe
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_help.text: The number in the compartment shows the internal height of the compartment. Please always calculate compartment heights starting at the top and working downwards. You change the height of an entire section using the model.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_widt.title: Schrank Schritt 2 Breite (cm)
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_widt.headline: Column width
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_widt.text: You can change the inner width of each column under the option "Width (cm)" to combine narrow and wide columns in a cabinet.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_heig.title: Schrank Schritt 2 H=C3=B6he (cm)
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_heig.headline: Column height
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_heig.text: Under the option "Height (cm)" you can define the total height from the floor level for each individual column. In this way you can configure a step cabinet or a sideboard cabinet combination.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_cubb.title: Schrank Schritt 2 F=C3=A4cher
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_cubb.headline: Compartments per column (removeable shelves)
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_cubb.text: Under the section "compartments" you can define the number of compartments in each individual column. This also automatically determines the number of removable shelves in your cupboard (number of compartments - 1). If you want to change the height of a single shelf, click on the numerical value in it and enter the desired height.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_sock.title: Schrank Schritt 2 Sockel
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_sock.headline: Plinth
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_sock.text: We offer cabinets optionally with or without plinths. The plinth has a regular height of 7 cm. This is included in the total height of your furniture product.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_help.title: Schrank Schritt 3 Hilfe
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_help.text: For a CD shelf you need a depth of 15 cm; for document files the depth should be at least 25 cm. The unit is assembled on its side. If you wish to have a door that covers multiple compartments, drag with the mouse over the relevant compartments to select them.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_help.title: Schrank Schritt 4 Hilfe
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_help.text:
Our shelving strip with mounting holes lets you adjust the shelf heights in increments of 32 mm (the spacing between each hole). If you choose mounting holes, a central row of shelves will nevertheless be fixed in place in larger units to maintain stability. 

You can however vary the positions of all other shelves in the unit with the option to alternate  your shelving arrangement at a later date.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-column_coun.title: Schrank Schritt 2 Anzahl der Spalten insgesamt
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-column_coun.headline: Total number of sections
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-column_coun.text: Specify how many vertical sections you would like in your wardrobe unit. An initial design is suggested in the configurator, which you can then modify freely.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_hand.title: Schrank Schritt 3 =C3=96ffnung/Griff Eingriff
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_hand.text: With this option we will cut a small opening in the door. You can then use this to open the door with your fingers.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_hand.title: Schrank Schritt 3 =C3=96ffnung/Griff Metallgriff
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_hand.text: A chrome metal handle with a simple and stylish design helps you open the door.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_hand.title: Schrank Schritt 3 =C3=96ffnung/Griff Pushtoopen
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_hand.text: Our 'push-to-open' technology can be activated with a light push. There is no need for door knobs, meaning doors can remain a subtle and integrated feature.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_hand.title: Schrank Schritt 3 =C3=96ffnung/Griff Knauf
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_hand.text: A chrome metal door knob in a simple design provides a stylish finish.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_rear.title: Schrank Schritt 4 R=C3=BCckwand
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_rear.text: Please choose one of the rear wall panel colours. On request we can supply rear panels and veneer. Please note that the depth of the shelf is reduced with a rear wall panel by approximately 0.6 cm.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_loch.title: Schrank Schritt 4 Lochreihe
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_loch.headline: Shelving strips with mounting holes
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_loch.text: The vertical hole strip allows you more freedom in arranging your individual shelves. Holes are drilled at 32 mm intervals, allowing you to adjust the sizes of the compartments to suit your needs. Please note that if you select a shelving strip with mounting holes, any compartment heights you have previously set will no longer be relevant. In high shelving units, a horizontal compartment row is also fixed in place to retain the best possible stability.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_raum.title: Schrank Schritt 4 Raumteiler
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_raum.text: If you selected a plinth in step 2 and choose the room divider option, the plinth baseboard will be fitted on both sides of your product.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_hang.title: Schrank Schritt 4 H=C3=A4ngeregal
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_hang.headline: Wall shelf – for shelves without pinth
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_hang.text: If you select this option, a wall fixing will be supplied with your unit.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_fusl.title: Schrank Schritt 4 Fu=C3=9Fleiste
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_fusl.headline: Skirting board cut-out
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_fusl.text: We can create a cut-out for your skirting board to enable the shelving unit to align with the wall. Simply specify the height and depth of the cut-out required in cms. If the height of the cut-out is more than 7 cm  and you decide to combine it with a additional rear wall panel, please contact a consultant, as this affects the construction of the furniture piece.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_durc.title: Durchgehende Deck-/Bodenplatte
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_durc.headline: Continuous top and bottom plate
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_4_durc.text: We build shelves column by column as standard. On request we also offer continuous top and bottom plates. In this case a minimum space of 4 cm to the ceiling is required for installation. Please note that the top and bottom panels as well as the sides are divided if the following dimensions are exceeded: solid wood: 298 cm, MDF/real wood veneer: 275 cm, plywood: 248 cm, chip: 272 cm. The division is based on the maximum panel dimensions available as per industry standard. Please contact us in this regard so that we can discuss where to divide the panels. Otherwise, we will divide the panels in a way that is beneficial for the construction.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_materi.title: Schrank Material - Furnier
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_materi.headline: Veneer
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_materi.text: Our real wood veneers are an economical alternative to natural solid wood. Our veneers are finished with natural oil.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_materi.title: Schrank Material - Massive
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_materi.headline: Solid wood
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_materi.text: Our selection of solid woods are extremely durable and stable. All wood types are available with a natural, transparent oil treatment. In some cases certain wood types can also be treated with coloured oil.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_materi.title: Schrank Material - MDF
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_materi.headline: MDF
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_materi.text: MDF is a very stable and economical  wood alternative. We offer this material in a variety of coatings as well as painted RAL colors.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_elem.title: Schrank Schritt 3 Element type
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_elem.text: For our doors and drawers, we use the 'push-to-open' technology as a standard opening mechanism. Unless selected, there are no handles and opening and closing doors and draws is activated with little pressure.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_door.title: Regale Schritt 3 einfache T=C3=BCr
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_door.text: The simple rotary door is located within a column and can be planned over several compartments. A door can be made up to a width of 60 cm.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_door_b.title: Regale Schritt 3 Fl=C3=BCgelt=C3=BCr
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_door_b.text: Two doors within a column that can be opened to each other. We offer the hinged wing doors up to a column width of 130 cm.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_drawer.title: Regale Schritt 3 Schublade
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_drawer.text: The drawer can be opened with a half drawer. The construction is reduced by 4 cm in height, 4 cm in width and up to 7 cm in depth.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_inner.title: Regale Schritt 3 Innenliegend
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_inner.text: The front of the door or drawer is located inside the compartment. The compartment is reduced in depth by approximately 2 cm.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_outer.title: Regale Schritt 3 Aufliegend
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_outer.text: The front of the door or drawer is rests on the shelf. The edges of the shelf are half covered by the front.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_dekor.title: Regale Schritt 1 Dekore
bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_dekor.headline: Chipboard decor
bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_dekor.text: Under decors you will find our coated finish options.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_lackie.title: Regale Schritt 1 Lackierte oberfl=C3=A4chen
bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_lackie.headline: Lacquered Surfaces
bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_lackie.text: We offer high quality medium density fibreboard in a multiple of lacquered finishes.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_massiv.title: Regale Schritt 1 Massivholz
bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_massiv.headline: Solid wood
bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_massiv.text: Our selection of solid woods are extremely durable and stable. All wood types are available with a natural, transparent oil treatment. In some cases certain wood types can also be treated with coloured oil.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_furnie.title: Regale Schritt 1 Furniere
bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_furnie.headline: Veneer
bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_furnie.text: Our real wood veneers are an economical alternative to solid wood. Our real wood veneers are attached to high-quality MDF boards. All veneers are treated with natural oils.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_door_f.title: Regale Schritt 3 Klappt=C3=BCr
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_door_f.headline: Hinged doors
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_door_f.text: Our custom door option is equipped with two hinges and a damper.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_multip.title: Regale Schritt 1 Multiplex
bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_multip.headline: Plywood
bubble-configurator-regale-step_1_multip.text: Plywood is a great option, a combination between wood and a coated surface.

bubble-configurator-tableplate-general-t.title: Tischplatte tooltip
bubble-configurator-tableplate-general-t.text: Configure a table plate in different materials, as well as various shapes and sizes.

bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_lock.title: Regale Schritt 3 T=C3=BCrschloss
bubble-configurator-regale-step_3_lock.text: Our premium quality locks are made from steel and include 2 keys.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_draw.title: Schrank Schritt 3 Innenschublade
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_draw.headline: Inside drawer
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_draw.text:
Requires a depth of at least 32 cm.

The width of the compartment must be between 20 and 120 cm.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_trou.title: Schrank Schritt 3 Hosenhalter links
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_trou.headline: Trouser holder left
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_trou.text: The trouser holder requires a depth of at least 50 cm.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_trou.title: Schrank Schritt 3 Hosenhalter rechts
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_trou.headline: Trouser holder right
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_trou.text: The trouser holder requires a depth of at least 50 cm.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_rail.title: Schrank Schritt 3 Kleiderstange
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_rail.headline: Clothes rail
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_rail.text: Choose a clothes rail to store your clothing items.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_pant.title: Schrank Schritt 3 Kleiderlift
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_pant.headline: Garment lift
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_pant.text:
Requires a depth of at least 55 cm.

The width of the compartment must be between 55 cm and 120 cm.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_spli.title: Schrank Schritt 3 senkrechte Teilung des Faches
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_spli.headline: Vertical division
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_3_spli.text: To make better use of the storage space, you can divide the compartment vertically.

bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_cove.title: Schrank Schritt 2 Blendleisten f=C3=BCr Einbauschrank
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_cove.headline: Cover strips for built-in cupboards
bubble-configurator-wardrobe-step_2_cove.text:
The cover strips are screwed from the inside, attaching the side walls and the cover plates. This increases the external dimensions by approximately 3 cm and reduces the distances to the walls required for installation.

Plan the height and width of your cabinet with an installation distance of 2,5 / 2,8 cm each, as this results in a perfect shadow gap. To utilize this option you need a flat floor and straight walls!

bubble-configurator-tableplate-straighte.title: Tischplatte Gratleisten
bubble-configurator-tableplate-straighte.text: In order to avoid any swelling or shrinkage of the wood we can add straightening metal battens beneath your table top.

bubble-conf2-step1-dimensions.title: Conf2 Ma=C3=9Fe
bubble-conf2-step1-dimensions.headline: Specify External Dimensions
bubble-conf2-step1-dimensions.text:
Determine the exact external dimensions of your shelf down to the centimeter. The width of the shelf can range between 30 and 600 cm, and the height between 30 and 300 cm, while the depth can be adjusted between 15 and 60 cm.
Please note during planning: For structural reasons, the top/bottom panels and side panels must be split if the following dimensions are exceeded:
- Solid wood: 300 cm
- MDF and real wood veneer: 275 cm
- Multiplex: 245 cm
- Premium decor chipboard: 275 cm
Feel free to inform us where you would like the splits to occur.

Are you planning a shelf for a niche or designing it to reach up to the ceiling? Please include the following installation allowances: 3 cm to one side and 3 cm to the ceiling. For more information regarding necessary installation clearances, please visit Services  Help - How to measure correctly. The options "Wall Mount (Hanging Shelf)" and "Room Divider" can also be selected in this step.

Special Request: Do you need your shelf in custom dimensions? Contact our expert interior design team – we are happy to assist you with your planning.

bubble-conf2-step1-material.title: Conf2 Material
bubble-conf2-step1-material.headline: Select Material
bubble-conf2-step1-material.text:
Choose your desired material with just one click. You can select from 12 solid woods, painted or coated MDF panels, real wood veneers, premium decor chipboards, or multiplex. If you opt for solid wood or real wood veneer, you can also choose from various oils/finishes. Painted MDF can be configured in over 200 RAL colors.

For more information about our materials, please visit Services  Help - Materials  samples.

Tip: Can't decide on a material? You can order up to two free wood samples to be delivered to your home.

Additionally, in this step, you can specify the material thickness for your shelf. Depending on the material and surface treatment, the thickness is approximately 1.8 to 2.0 cm or 2.8 to 3.0 cm. Your entered external dimensions will remain unchanged, and all tolerances will be distributed symmetrically.

bubble-conf2-step1-thickness.title: Conf2 Regale Schritt 1 Materialst=C3=A4rke
bubble-conf2-step1-thickness.headline: Specify the material thickness
bubble-conf2-step1-thickness.text: Determine the material thickness for your shelf. Depending on the material and surface treatment, the material thickness is approx. 1.8 to 2.0 cm or approx. 2.8 to 3.0 cm. The external dimensions you have selected remain unchanged.

bubble-conf2-columns_settings.title: Conf2 Einstellung f=C3=BCr Spalten
bubble-conf2-columns_settings.headline: Columns  compartments
bubble-conf2-columns_settings.text:
Use the slider to plan the number of columns and compartments for your shelf. In the 3D view, both the column size and the compartment size of your shelf can be individually adjusted.
Additionally, in this step, you have the option to select a row of holes and/or a back panel.
If you would like to learn more about these options, hover your mouse over the info icons.

bubble-conf2-step1-socket.title: Conf2 Regale Schritt 2 Sockel
bubble-conf2-step1-socket.headline: Adjust base
bubble-conf2-step1-socket.text:
You can design your shelves with or without a base. If you choose a base, you can configure its height between 7 and 15 cm. The overall height of your shelf will remain unchanged.
In this step, you also have the option to select a skirting board cut-out or a height adjuster.

Tip: For stability reasons, we recommend a base for your shelf, a back panel (selectable in Step 4 of the configurator), or alternatively, wall mounting.

bubble-conf2-step2-doors_settings.title: Conf2 Einstellung f=C3=BCr T=C3=BCren  Schubladen
bubble-conf2-step2-doors_settings.headline: Doors  compartments
bubble-conf2-step2-doors_settings.text:
Select a compartment with one click. If you want to select several compartments, drag the mouse over the desired compartments.

Depth for furniture with fronts:
Surface-mounted fronts are always added to the specified depth.

bubble-conf2-step2-door_type.title: Conf2 Regale Schritt 2 Element type
bubble-conf2-step2-door_type.headline: Add Doors  Drawers
bubble-conf2-step2-door_type.text:
You can plan drawers and various types of doors with a single click on the respective compartment. If you want to plan a door across multiple vertical compartments, select the desired compartments by holding down the mouse button. By default, our doors are equipped with push-to-open, but you can alternatively choose from five different handles in various colors. You can also specify the material for the doors or drawers and decide whether the door or drawer should be inset or overlaying.

Furniture fronts are manufactured with a material thickness of 2 cm. For overlaying fronts, the specified depth increases by 2 cm, while for inset fronts, the usable depth is reduced by 2 cm. If the inset fronts are made of solid wood, we add stabilization strips with a thickness of 2 cm, which further reduces the usable depth by 2 cm.
If you plan your shelf in solid wood, the drawer boxes are made of multiplex, and the drawer fronts are made of your selected solid wood. If you configure your furniture in any other material (excluding solid wood or real wood veneer), your drawer boxes will be white. If a front option cannot be selected, the required dimensions for the compartment will be displayed when you hover over it with the mouse.

Tip: Fronts can also be made from a material different from the body of the shelf. A particularly popular combination is a solid wood body with painted MDF fronts.

bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options.title: Conf2 Zusatzoptionen
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options.headline: Add additional options
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options.text:
In the final step, you can enhance your custom-made shelf with various details. For example, you can add cable outlets or a stainless steel ladder to your design. If you have special requests, you can include them directly in this step by selecting the 'Special Requests' field and noting your request.

For information on all special requests, please visit Services  help - Product details  special requests.

bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-lo.title: Conf2 Regale Schritt 4 Lochreihe
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-lo.headline: Strip with mounting holes
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-lo.text:
IMPORTANT: If you select a strip with mounting holes, any compartment heights that you have previously set will be overridden. In higher shelving, a horizontal compartment row is also fixed in place to maintain optimal stability. We are happy to support you with any questions or concerns.

The mounting holes will be placed with 32 mm space in between so that you can change the position of your shelves later on at home.

bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ha.title: Conf2 Regale Schritt 4 H=C3=A4ngeregal
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ha.headline: Hanging furniture - only available for shelves without a base
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ha.text:
If your shelving unit is to be used hanging against a wall, mounting brackets can be built into the vertical side panels to fix your furniture in place. Our expert carpenters determine the number and position of each bracket to ensure weight is distributed optimally. The maximum depth for hanging shelves is 50 cm. Hanging shelfs cannot be ordered with a back wall or as room divider.

Please note: 
Only available for shelves without a base.
Wall shelves can only be mounted on solid walls.

bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-fu.title: Conf2 Regale Schritt 4 Fu=C3=9Fleiste
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-fu.headline: Skirting board cut-out
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-fu.text: A skirting board cut-out allows your furniture piece to stand flat against the wall and bypass any skirting board that may interfere with the arrangement. Only possible for shelfs with plinth or without back panel.

bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-de.title: Conf2 Deckenverspanner
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-de.text: The ceiling clamps can be used for fastening your product to the ceiling. The distance to the ceiling must be between 90-109 mm, so it is best to plan with a distance of 10 cm.

bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ra.title: Conf2 Regale Schritt 4 Raumteiler
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ra.headline: Room divider
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ra.text:
Available with a minimum depth of 30 cm, the room divider is manufactured to be identical on both sides (including the baseboard, if selected). 

Please note: 
Drawers are only accessible on one side of the product. The back of the drawer consists of a solid back panel that matches the look of the drawer front.

bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ru.title: Conf2 Regale Schritt 4 R=C3=BCckwand
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ru.headline: Back wall panel
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ru.text:
For shelves made of premium decor, the back panel consists of an 8 or 10 mm thick chipboard. For all other materials, a 3 mm thick hardboard panel is used. The usable depth is reduced by 19 mm for all back panels. 
Note: For 1 and 2-column shelving units, we strongly recommend including a back panel.

bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ho.title: Conf2 H=C3=B6henversteller
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ho.headline: Height adjustment
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ho.text:
The feature can be added to a shelving unit with a minimum height of 180 cm and a baseboard height of up to 9 cm. Height adjusters make it easy to compensate for any unevenness in your flooring up to a height of 2.5 cm.

Please note: 
The total height of the furniture will increase by 0.55 cm when fitted with height adjusters.

bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-du.title: Conf2 Durchgehende Deck-/Bodenplatte
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-du.headline: Continuous top and bottom plate
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-du.text: We build shelves column by column as standard. On request we also offer continuous top and bottom plates. In this case a minimum space of 4 cm to the ceiling is required for installation. Please note that the top and bottom panels as well as the sides are divided if the following dimensions are exceeded: solid wood: 298 cm, MDF/real wood veneer: 275 cm, multiplex: 248 cm, chip: 272 cm. The division is based on the maximum panel dimensions available as per industry standard. Please contact us in this regard so that we can discuss where to divide the panels. Otherwise, we will divide the panels in a way that is beneficial for the construction.

bubble-conf2-step3-special_wish.title: Conf2 Weitere Sonderw=C3=BCnsche
bubble-conf2-step3-special_wish.headline: Additional special requests
bubble-conf2-step3-special_wish.text: If you have any further special requests, please do not hesitate to contact us free of charge.

bubble-conf2-step2-settings_all.title: Conf2 Einstellungen f=C3=BCr alle Fronten =C3=BCbernehmen
bubble-conf2-step2-settings_all.text: If you have selected this option, all fronts will be changed. If you want to customize the fronts individually, deselect this option.

bubble-configurator-rboden-step_material.title: Regalb=C3=B6den Holzart w=C3=A4hlen
bubble-configurator-rboden-step_material.headline: Material
bubble-configurator-rboden-step_material.text: Select the material you require.  We also offer many materials in different colours.

bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-co.title: Conf2 Schrank Schritt 2 Blendleisten f=C3=BCr Einbauschrank
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-co.headline: Cover strip for fitted wardrobes
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-co.text:
The cover strips provide your wardrobe with a seamless finish, covering the mounting distance space between the wardrobe and the wall. 

Please note: 
This feature is added to the exterior dimensions (+3 cm) and reduces the distance to the wall required for installation. If you plan with an installation distance of 2.5 cm in height from the wardrobe to the ceiling and a distance of 3 cm on each side of your product. The cover stips will fill this mounting distance perfectly. 

Flat floors and straight walls are required to utilise this feature.

bubble-wardrobe2-inner-options.title: Wardrobe 2 Inner options
bubble-wardrobe2-inner-options.headline: Design interior features
bubble-wardrobe2-inner-options.text: In this step, you can add the ideal interior features to your custom wardrobe with a single click on the desired compartment. If an option cannot be selected, the required dimensions for the compartment will be displayed when you hover over it with the mouse.

bubble-wardrobe2-columns_settings.title: Wardrobe 2 Einstellung f=C3=BCr Spalten
bubble-wardrobe2-columns_settings.headline: Columns  compartments
bubble-wardrobe2-columns_settings.text:
Use the slider to determine the number of columns and compartments for your wardrobe. In the 3D view, both the column size and compartment size can be individually adjusted.
If you want to remain flexible with the compartment layout, you can also select rows of holes in this step.

bubble-wardrobe2-step1-dimensions.title: Wardrobe 2 Ma=C3=9Fe
bubble-wardrobe2-step1-dimensions.headline: Specify external dimensions
bubble-wardrobe2-step1-dimensions.text:
In the first step, you can determine the external dimensions of your custom-made wardrobe to the exact centimeter. The height of the wardrobe can range between 40 and 275 cm, the width between 37 and 600 cm, and the depth can be adjusted between 20 and 110 cm.
If you want to design a ceiling-high wardrobe or sloped ceiling wardrobe as a built-in solution, we recommend maintaining an installation clearance of 3 cm to the ceiling and one side. If you plan to add sliding doors to your custom wardrobe, please allow for an installation clearance of 5 cm to the ceiling and 3 cm to the sides.
For more information, please visit Services  Help - How to measure correctly or book an on-site measurement service.
Please note that for structural reasons, top and bottom panels made from MDF, premium decor chipboards, or real wood veneer must be split at lengths exceeding 275 cm. Feel free to inform our interior design team where you would prefer the split to occur.
All of our wardrobes are equipped with a back panel, which reduces the usable depth by 2 cm.
Special Request: Do you need a wider or taller piece of furniture? Contact our expert interior design team – our advisors are happy to assist you with your furniture planning.

bubble-wardrobe2-step1-material.title: Wardrobe 2 Material
bubble-wardrobe2-step1-material.headline: Select material
bubble-wardrobe2-step1-material.text:
Here you can choose your desired material for your custom-made wardrobe from 14 premium decor chipboards, painted MDF panels, or real wood veneers. Painted MDF can be configured in over 200 RAL colors.
For more information about our materials, please visit Services  Help - Materials  samples.
Tip: Can't decide on a material? You can order up to two free wood samples to be delivered to your home.

bubble-wardrobe2-step1-socket.title: Wardrobe 2 Regale Schritt 2 Sockel
bubble-wardrobe2-step1-socket.headline: Adjust base
bubble-wardrobe2-step1-socket.text:
In this step, you can set the base height of your wardrobe between 7 and 14 cm. The height of the base is already included in the total height of your wardrobe. If you require a skirting board cut-out in the base, this can also be selected in this step.
Additionally: All wardrobes from Pickawood are equipped with height adjusters, allowing you to compensate for uneven floors by up to 1.5 cm.

bubble-wardrobe2-step1-thickness.title: Wardrobe 2 Regale Schritt 1 Materialst=C3=A4rke
bubble-wardrobe2-step1-thickness.headline: Material thickness
bubble-wardrobe2-step1-thickness.text: Depending on the surface treatment, the material thickness is approx. 1.8 - 2.0 cm or approx. 2.8 - 3.0 cm. Your entered external dimensions remain unchanged.

bubble-wardrobe2-step2-door_type.title: Wardrobe 2 - 7 T=C3=BCren  Schubladen hinzuf=C3=BCgen
bubble-wardrobe2-step2-door_type.headline: Add doors  drawers
bubble-wardrobe2-step2-door_type.text:
You can configure drawers and various types of doors with a single click on the desired compartment.
Note: At Pickawood, wardrobe fronts are always produced as overlaying, so the material thickness of 2 cm is added to the total depth. If you choose drawers, the drawer boxes of your wardrobe will be white, but the material or color of the drawer fronts can be adjusted here.
If you want to plan a door across multiple vertical compartments, select the desired compartments by holding down the mouse button. Once you have selected a door or drawer, you can specify both the material and the door handles (choose from five different handle designs).
Tip: Fronts can also be made from a material different than the body of the wardrobe.

bubble-wardrobe2-step2-doors_settings.title: Wardrobe 2 Einstellung f=C3=BCr T=C3=BCren  Schubladen
bubble-wardrobe2-step2-doors_settings.headline: Doors  Drawers
bubble-wardrobe2-step2-doors_settings.text: You can select any compartment to add a door or drawer. If you want to add doors over multiple compartments you can click below the column to mark all compartments above or click them one by one.

bubble-wardrobe2-step2-settings_all.title: Wardrobe 2 Einstellungen f=C3=BCr alle Fronten =C3=BCbernehmen
bubble-wardrobe2-step2-settings_all.text: If you have selected this option, all fronts will be changed. If you want to customize the fronts individually, deselect this option.

bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.title: Wardrobe 2 Zusatzoptionen
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.headline: Add additional options
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.text:
Every wardrobe we make includes free back panels and height adjusters. Additionally, you have the option to add the following to your wardrobe:
- Cover panels for a built-in wardrobe
- Cut-out without cover
- Cut-out with cable outlet (8x8 cm) in aluminum look
- Cut-out with cable outlet (16x8 cm) in aluminum look
You can find information about other special requests under Services  help - Product details  special requests.

bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.title: Wardrobe 2 Schrank Schritt 2 Blendleisten f=C3=BCr Einbauschrank
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.text:
The cover strips are screwed from the inside, attaching the side walls and the cover plates. This increases the external dimensions by approximately 3 cm and reduces the distances to the walls required for installation.

Plan the height and width of your cabinet with an installation distance of 2,8 cm each, as this results in a perfect shadow gap. To utilize this option you need a flat floor and straight walls!

bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.title: Wardrobe 2 Deckenverspanner
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.text: The ceiling clamps can be used for fastening your product to the ceiling. The distance to the ceiling must be between 90-109 mm, so it is best to plan with a distance of 10 cm.

bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.title: Wardrobe 2 Durchgehende Deck-/Bodenplatte
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.headline: Continuous top and bottom plate
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.text: We build shelves column by column as standard. On request we also offer continuous top and bottom plates. In this case a minimum space of 4 cm to the ceiling is required for installation. Please note that the top and bottom panels as well as the sides are divided if the following dimensions are exceeded: MDF/chip/real wood veneer: 272 cm. The division is based on the maximum panel dimensions available as per industry standard. Please contact us in this regard so that we can discuss where to divide the panels. Otherwise, we will divide the panels in a way that is advantageous for the construction.

bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.title: Wardrobe 2 Regale Schritt 4 Fu=C3=9Fleiste
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.headline: Skirting board cut-out
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.text: A skirting board cut-out allows your furniture piece to stand flat against the wall and bypass any skirting board that may interfere with the arrangement.

bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.title: Wardrobe 2 Regale Schritt 4 H=C3=A4ngeregal
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.headline: Only available for shelves without plinth. Hanging shelves are not available as room dividers.
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.text: If you select this option, a wall fixing will be supplied with your unit.

bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.title: Wardrobe 2 H=C3=B6henversteller
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.headline: Height adjustment
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.text: We install high-quality height adjusters in all our cabinets. With height adjusters you are able to align the height evenly. The plinth cover is attached at the front so that the height adjuster is not visible from the outside. The height can then be adjusted up to 2.5 cm.

bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.title: Wardrobe 2 Regale Schritt 4 Lochreihe
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.headline: Strip with mounting holes
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.text: IMPORTANT: If you select a strip with mounting holes, any compartment heights that you have previously set will be overridden. In higher shelving, a horizontal compartment row is also fixed in place to maintain optimal stability. We are happy to support you with any questions or concerns.

bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.title: Wardrobe 2 Regale Schritt 4 Raumteiler
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.headline: Room divider
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.text: For the room divider option we manufacture the baseboard (if selected) to be included on both sides of the product. In addition, all doors are mirrored, so that you can use them identically on both sides. Drawers are offered exclusively on one side of the product. The back of the drawer consists of a solid back panel that matches the look of the drawer front.

bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.title: Wardrobe 2 Regale Schritt 4 R=C3=BCckwand
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.headline: Back wall panel
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.text: Cupboards are always manufactured with a back panel. For Premium D=C3=A9cor, this has a thickness of 8 or 10 mm, for all other materials 3 mm. The usable depth is reduced by 19 mm for all back panels. With Premium d=C3=A9cors, the colour of the back panel matches the rest of the wardrobe. Rear panels for real wood veneer and lacquered wardrobes are always white.

bubble-wardrobe2-step3-special_wish.title: Wardrobe 2 Weitere Sonderw=C3=BCnsche
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-special_wish.headline: Additional special requests
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-special_wish.text: If you have any further special requests, please do not hesitate to contact us free of charge.

bubble-conf2-cubbies_settings.title: Conf2 Einstellung f=C3=BCr F=C3=A4cher
bubble-conf2-cubbies_settings.headline: Define the compartments
bubble-conf2-cubbies_settings.text: Use the slider to set the number of compartments. In the 3D view, you can add the required number of compartments for each column. Here, the height and width of the respective compartments can also be adjusted.

bubble-wardrobe2-cubbies_settings.title: Wardrobe 2 Einstellung f=C3=BCr F=C3=A4cher
bubble-wardrobe2-cubbies_settings.headline: Define the compartments
bubble-wardrobe2-cubbies_settings.text:
Use the slider to set the number of compartments. In the 3D view, you can add the required number of compartments for each column. Here, the height and width of the respective compartments can also be adjusted. You can adjust the height of each compartment by holding down the mouse button on the arrows.
Tip: If you would like a flexible shelving option when dividing the compartments, you can select the "Strip with mounting holes" option in the 8th step of the configurator. This allows you to rearrange shelves even after assembly.

bubble-sideboard2-columns_settings.title: Sideboard 2 Einstellung f=C3=BCr Spalten
bubble-sideboard2-columns_settings.headline: Columns  compartments
bubble-sideboard2-columns_settings.text:
Use the slider to plan the number of columns and compartments for your sideboard. In the 3D view, both the column size and compartment size can be individually adjusted.
Additionally, in this step, you have the option to select a row of holes and/or a back panel.

bubble-sideboard2-cubbies_settings.title: Sideboard 2 Einstellung f=C3=BCr F=C3=A4cher
bubble-sideboard2-cubbies_settings.headline: Define the compartments
bubble-sideboard2-cubbies_settings.text: Use the slider to set the number of compartments. In the 3D view, you can add the required number of compartments for each column. Here, the height and width of the respective compartments can also be adjusted.

bubble-sideboard2-step1-dimensions.title: Sideboard 2 Ma=C3=9Fe
bubble-sideboard2-step1-dimensions.headline: Specify external dimensions
bubble-sideboard2-step1-dimensions.text:
In this step, you can determine the external dimensions of your custom-made sideboard, planning them to the exact centimeter. The height of the sideboard can range between 30 and 300 cm, and the width between 30 and 600 cm, while the depth can be adjusted between 15 and 60 cm.
Please note during your planning: For structural reasons, the top/bottom panels and side panels must be split if the following dimensions are exceeded:
- Solid wood: 300 cm
- MDF and real wood veneer: 275 cm
- Multiplex: 245 cm
- Premium decor chipboard: 275 cm
Feel free to let us know where you would like the splits to occur.

Are you planning a piece of furniture for a niche? Please allow for the following installation clearances: 3 cm to one side and 3 cm to the ceiling. For more information regarding necessary installation clearances, please visit  Services  Help - How to measure correctly or book an on-site measurement service.
The option "wall mount (hanging sideboard)" can also be selected in this step.

bubble-sideboard2-step1-material.title: Sideboard 2 Material
bubble-sideboard2-step1-material.headline: Select material
bubble-sideboard2-step1-material.text:
Choose your desired material with just one click. You can select from 12 solid woods, painted or coated MDF panels, real wood veneers, premium decor chipboards, or multiplex. If you opt for solid wood or real wood veneer, you can also choose from various oils/finishes. Painted MDF can be configured in over 200 RAL colors.

For more information about our materials, please visit Services  Help - Materials  samples.

Tip: Can't decide on a material? You can order up to two free wood samples to be delivered to your home.

Additionally, in this step, you can specify the material thickness for your sideboard. Depending on the material and surface treatment, the thickness is approximately 1.8 to 2.0 cm or 2.8 to 3.0 cm. Your entered external dimensions will remain unchanged, and all tolerances will be distributed symmetrically.

bubble-sideboard2-step1-socket.title: Sideboard 2 Regale Schritt 2 Sockel
bubble-sideboard2-step1-socket.headline: Adjust feet or base
bubble-sideboard2-step1-socket.text:
You can design your sideboards with a base, without a base, or with a variety of furniture feet. Choose from a selection of 11 furniture feet or frame constructions. If you opt for a base, you can configure its height between 7 and 15 cm. The overall height of your furniture will remain unchanged when adjusting the base height.
If you select a base for your custom sideboard and require a skirting board cut-out, you can choose this option in the same step of the configurator.

bubble-sideboard2-step1-thickness.title: Sideboard 2 Regale Schritt 1 Materialst=C3=A4rke
bubble-sideboard2-step1-thickness.headline: Specify the material thickness
bubble-sideboard2-step1-thickness.text: Determine the material thickness for your sideboard. Depending on the material and surface treatment, the material thickness is approx. 1.8 to 2.0 cm or approx. 2.8 to 3.0 cm. The external dimensions you have selected remain unchanged.

bubble-sideboard2-step2-door_type.title: Sideboard 2 Regale Schritt 2 Element type
bubble-sideboard2-step2-door_type.headline: Select the doors  drawers
bubble-sideboard2-step2-door_type.text:
Our doors are fitted with our push-to-open function as standard. Alternatively, you can choose from 5 different handles in different colours and finishes. You can determine both the material of the doors or drawers, as well as decide whether your fronts should be interior fitted or surface-mounted.
Drawers and doors are manufactured with a material thickness of 2 cm. For surface-mounted fronts, the specified depth increases by 2 cm, while the usable depth decreases by 2 cm for interior fitted options. If the interior fitted fronts are made of solid wood, we apply 2 cm thick stabilizing strips, which reduce the usable depth by another 2 cm.
If you are planning a solid wood finish for your sideboard, the drawers will be made of plywood, with the drawer fronts made from your chosen solid wood type. If you select one of our additional materials (excluding solid wood or real wood veneer) for your furniture, your drawers will be produced with a white finish.
Please note that the usable depth of the drawer is reduced by approx. 7-10 cm compared to the total depth of the unit. Drawer rails, back panels or internal or surface-mounted fronts, for example, have an influence on the usable depth. Please contact us for more detailed information.
Tip: You can choose fronts made from a different material than the furniture structure. A popular option is the combination of a solid wood structure with MDF varnished fronts.

bubble-sideboard2-step2-doors_settings.title: Sideboard 2 Einstellung f=C3=BCr T=C3=BCren  Schubladen
bubble-sideboard2-step2-doors_settings.headline: Doors  compartments
bubble-sideboard2-step2-doors_settings.text:
Select a compartment with one click. If you want to select several compartments, drag the mouse over the desired compartments.

Depth for furniture with fronts:
Outside fronts (in step 2) are always added to the specified depth.

bubble-sideboard2-step2-settings_all.title: Sideboard 2 Einstellungen f=C3=BCr alle Fronten =C3=BCbernehmen
bubble-sideboard2-step2-settings_all.text: If you have selected this option, all fronts will be changed. If you want to customize the fronts individually, deselect this option.

bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.title: Sideboard 2 Zusatzoptionen
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.headline: Add additional options
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.text:
In the final step, you can enhance your custom-made sideboard with various details. For example, you can add cable outlets or a corner construction to your design. If you have special requests, you can include them directly in this step by selecting the "Special Requests" field and noting your request.
For information on all special requests, please visit Services  help - Product details  special requests.

bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.title: Sideboard 2 Schrank Schritt 2 Blendleisten f=C3=BCr Einbauschrank
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.headline: Cover strips for built-in cupboards
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.text:
The cover strips are screwed from the inside, attaching the side walls and the cover plates. This increases the external dimensions by approximately 3 cm and reduces the distances to the walls required for installation.

Plan the height and width of your cabinet with an installation distance of 2,5 / 2,8 cm each, as this results in a perfect shadow gap. To utilize this option you need a flat floor and straight walls!

bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.title: Sideboard 2 Deckenverspanner
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.text: The ceiling clamps can be used for fastening the product to the ceiling. The distance to the ceiling must be between 90-109 mm, so it is best to plan with a distance of 10 cm.

bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.title: Sideboard 2 Durchgehende Deck-/Bodenplatte
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.headline: Continuous top and bottom plate
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.text: We build shelves column by column as standard. On request we also offer continuous top and bottom plates. In this case a minimum space of 4 cm to the ceiling is required for installation. Please note that the top and bottom panels as well as the sides are divided if the following dimensions are exceeded: solid wood: 298 cm, MDF/real wood veneer: 275 cm, multiplex: 248 cm, chip: 272 cm. The division is based on the maximum panel dimensions available as per industry standard. Please contact us in this regard so that we can discuss where to divide the panels. Otherwise, we will divide the panels in a way that is beneficial for the construction of your product.

bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.title: Sideboard 2 Regale Schritt 4 Fu=C3=9Fleiste
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.headline: Skirting board cut-out
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.text: A skirting board cut-out allows your furniture piece to stand flat against the wall and bypass any skirting board that may interfere with the arrangement. Only possible for sideboards with plinth or without back panel.

bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.title: Sideboard 2 Regale Schritt 4 H=C3=A4ngeregal
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.headline: Hanging furniture - only available for sideboards without base or feet
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.text:
If your sideboard is to be used hanging against a wall, mounting brackets can be built into the vertical side panels to fix your furniture in place. Our expert carpenters determine the number and position of each bracket to ensure weight is distributed optimally. The maximum depth for hanging shelves is 50 cm. Hanging sideboards cannot be ordered with a back wall.

Please note: 
Only available for sideboards without a base or feet.
Hanging furniture can only be mounted on solid walls.

bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.title: Sideboard 2 H=C3=B6henversteller
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.headline: Only available for shelves with a pedestal
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.text: By opting for the height adjuster you can adapt the height of your product  to the floor. The height adjuster will generally add 0.55 cm to the total height of the shelf. The maximum load is 600 kg per stringer.

bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.title: Sideboard 2 Regale Schritt 4 Lochreihe
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.headline: Strip with mounting holes
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.text:
IMPORTANT: If you select a strip with mounting holes, any compartment heights that you have previously set will be overridden. In higher shelving, a horizontal compartment row is also fixed in place to maintain optimal stability. We are happy to support you with any questions or concerns.

The mounting holes will be placed with 32 mm space in between so that you can change the position of your shelves later on at home.

bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.title: Sideboard 2 Regale Schritt 4 Raumteiler
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.headline: Room divider
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.text: For the room divider option we manufacture the baseboard (if selected) to be included on both sides of the product. In addition, all doors are mirrored, so that you can use them identically on both sides. Drawers are offered exclusively on one side of the product. The back of the drawer consists of a solid back panel that matches the look of the drawer front.

bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.title: Sideboard 2 Regale Schritt 4 R=C3=BCckwand
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.headline: Back wall panel
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.text:
For sideboards made of premium decor, the back panel consists of an 8 or 10 mm thick chipboard. For all other materials, a 3 mm thick hardboard panel is used. The usable depth is reduced by 19 mm for all back panels. 

Note: For 1 and 2-column shelving units, we strongly recommend including a back panel.

bubble-sideboard2-step3-special_wish.title: Sideboard 2 Weitere Sonderw=C3=BCnsche
bubble-sideboard2-step3-special_wish.headline: Additional special requests
bubble-sideboard2-step3-special_wish.text: If you have any further special requests, please do not hesitate to contact us free of charge.

bubble-wardrobe2-step-restart.title: Wardrobe2 step 0 (restart)
bubble-wardrobe2-step-restart.text: Here you can choose a different wardrobe variation. Please be aware, if you do not save the configuration, your data will be lost.

bubble-conf2-responsive-welcome-help-she.title: Responsive intro bubble shelf
bubble-conf2-responsive-welcome-help-she.text: Here you can change the shelving according to your specific requirements.

bubble-conf2-responsive-welcome-help-sid.title: Responsive intro bubble sideboard
bubble-conf2-responsive-welcome-help-sid.text: Here you can change the sideboard according to your specific requirements.

bubble-conf2-responsive-welcome-help-war.title: Responsive intro bubble wardrobe
bubble-conf2-responsive-welcome-help-war.text: Here you can change the wardrobe according to your specific requirements.

bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ho.title: Conf2 H=C3=B6henversteller - Span/Dekor
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ho.headline: Only available for shelves with a pedestal
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ho.text: Height adjusters are possible for shelves with a minimum height of 181 cm and a plinth height up to 8 cm and 9 cm. Height adjusters make it easy to compensate for any unevenness with your product up to a height of 2.5 cm. The installation increases the total height of the unit by 0.55 cm.

bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.title: Sideboard 2 H=C3=B6henversteller - Span/Dekor
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.headline: Only available for sideboards with a pedestal
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.text: By opting for the height adjuster you can adapt the height of your product  to the floor. The height adjuster will generally add 0.55 cm to the total height of the shelf. The maximum load is 600 kg per stringer.

bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.title: Wardrobe 2 H=C3=B6henversteller - Span/Dekor
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.headline: Height adjustment
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.text: We install high-quality height adjusters in all our cabinets. Height adjusters make it easy to compensate for any unevenness in your flooring up to a height of 2.5 cm. The baseboard will cover the height adjuster at the front of the wardrobe so it is not visible after installation.

bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ha.title: Conf2 Regale Schritt 4 H=C3=A4ngeregal - Span/Dekor
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ha.headline: Hanging shelf - Only available for shelves without plinth
bubble-conf2-step3-additional_options-ha.text: When you configure a hanging shelf, wall brackets are built into the vertical side panels, which you can use to attach your shelf to the wall. The number and position of the brackets is selected by our carpenters so that the weight is optimally distributed. Notes: The maximum depth for hanging shelves is 50 cm. Hanging shelves are not available as room dividers or with a back panel. Hanging shelves may only be fitted to solid walls.

bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.title: Sideboard 2 Regale Schritt 4 H=C3=A4ngeregal - Span/Dekor
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.headline: Hanging sideboard - Only available for sideboards without plinth
bubble-sideboard2-step3-additional_optio.text: If you configure a hanging sideboard, wall brackets are built into the vertical side panels so that you can attach your sideboard to the wall. The number and position of the brackets is selected by our carpenters so that the weight is optimally distributed. Please note: The maximum depth for wall-mounted sideboards is 50 cm. Wall-mounted sideboards are not available with a rear panel. Hanging sideboards may only be attached to solid walls.

bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.title: Wardrobe 2 Regale Schritt 4 H=C3=A4ngeregal - Span/Dekor
bubble-wardrobe2-step3-additional_option.headline: Only available for shelves without plinth. Hanging shelves are not available as room dividers.
